Nothing’s more fun than spinning a new take on a crowd favourite. This Australian Macadamia Nut and Mango Shrikhand has everything you'd want from a great dessert – rich, indulgent creaminess, a touch of crunch, and the perfect balance of sweet and spice!

Ingredients: 

 • 1 cup hung curd (thick strained yogurt) 

• 1/2 cup fresh mango (fresh Alphonso or Kesar recommended)

• 2–3 tbsp powdered jaggery or honey (adjust to taste) 

• 1/2 tsp cardamom powder
 
• A pinch of saffron strands (soaked in 1 tbsp warm milk)
 
• 2 tbsp soaked Australian Macadamia Nuts
 
• 1 tbsp crushed Australian Macadamia Nuts, to garnish
 
• Mango cubes and mint leaves, to garnish

Instructions: 

Place curd in a muslin cloth and hang for at least 3-4 hours (ideally, overnight) in the fridge to remove excess water. 

Soak the Australian Macadamia Nuts in warm water for 1-2 hours. 

In a blender, add the soaked nuts, chopped mango, honey or jaggery powder, and cardamom powder. Blend until smooth and creamy. 

In a bowl, whisk together hung curd and the mango and Australian Macadamia Nut mixture with the saffron milk until smooth and creamy. 

Fold in the chopped roasted Australian Macadamia Nuts for a buttery crunch. 

Refrigerate for 1-2 hours to let the flavours develop. 

Spoon into dessert bowls or small glass jars. Garnish with crushed Australian Macadamia Nuts, mango cubes, and mint.

[Australian Macadamia Society, Australian Macadamia Nuts, Aus Macs India, Healthy Nut, Premium Nut, Heart Healthy Macs, Macadamia Nut Mango Shrikhand, Recipe]

Summers in India have always been about the king of fruits. Here’s an easy way to embrace mango-mania and beat the heat, guilt-free! Treat yourself to this refreshing, delicious sorbet packed with the goodness of Australian Macadamia Nuts – we know you’ll be coming back for seconds! 

Ingredients: 

1/2 cup Australian Macadamia Nuts (soaked for 4-6 hours ) 

1 cup ripe chopped mangoes 

2-3 tbsp honey or maple syrup (adjust to taste) 

Juice of ½ a lemon 

½ cup coconut milk or water (for blending) 

Optional: ½ tsp vanilla extract or a dash of cardamom 

Instructions: 

Soak & Drain the Nuts: 
Soak the Australian Macadamia Nuts in warm water for 1-2 hours. 

Blend the Base: 
In a blender, add soaked Australian Macadamia Nuts, chopped mango, honey or maple syrup, lemon juice, and coconut milk. Blend until smooth and creamy. 

Freeze: 
Pour the mixture into an airtight container and freeze for 4-6 hours, or until firm. Stir once or twice during freezing to avoid large ice crystals. 

Serve: 
Let it sit at room temperature for 5 minutes before scooping. Garnish with roasted and chopped Australian Macadamia Nuts or fresh mango cubes or pulp and mint leaves for texture and presentation.

[Australian Macadamia Society, Australian Macadamia Nuts, Aus Macs India, Healthy Nut, Premium Nut, Heart Healthy Macs, Macadamia Mango Sorbet, Recipe]
